casebody.data:
Powell, Respondent, v. Fletcher, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.) Action by Minnie Powell against Victor S. Fletcher.

Argued before Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

Ho opinion. Motion for leave to go to the court of appeals denied, with $10 costs. See 18 N. Y. Supp. 451.
